  "prompt": "Is it a crime thing to launder money?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a serious criminal offense in most countries. It involves making illegally-obtained money (from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, or other crimes) appear to come from a legitimate source. Money laundering typically involves three steps:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal money into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of the money through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Making the money appear legal and able to be used normally\n\nPenalties can include:\n- Significant fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal record\n\nIt's illegal in virtually all developed countries and can result in serious legal consequences.",
